              "free_text": [
                " A photoneutron source giving 220 keV neutrons",
                "was used to generate thermal neutron flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A sample of enriched uranium containing 35.5 microg of",
                "235U, prepared by the Berkeley method, was used as a",
                "standard, and a sample containing 16.8 microg of",
                "239Pu as determined by its alpha activity was used",
                "for the determination of sigma 239Pu."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Since thickness of the samples or inequality in their",
                "distribution is always a possible cause of error in",
                "measurements of this type we checked that our samples",
                "give the accepted value of sigma 239Pu/sigma 235U for",
                "thermal neutrons. This was done by surrounding the",
                "whole apparatus with a thick paraffin layer and",
                "measuring cadmium differences."
              ]
            }
          ],
